text:
Hotel yg keliatan dinamis banget, in a glance bisa ditangkep dr interior yg kekinian dan sooooo instagramable!
Banyak inovasi yg sangat kekinian tapi....
Cobalah utk disesuaikan atau dikomunikasikan kepada tamu ya?!
Ada bbrp hal yg jd perhatian,
1. Check in, inovasinya okelah sbg terobosan utk hemat dan cermat tanpa keycard yg sering hilang dan jd extra cost g penting. Tapi, pliss komunikasikan dgn tamu bhw perlu adanya instal aplikasi selama menginap, jd sblom walk in tamu sdh menginstal dan saat datang tinggal proses aja. Yg maksudnya biar mempercepat proses ci malah js selow gr2 instal2an ini.
2. Proses pemakaian aplikasi sbg kunci, akan sangat baik dan membantu kalau ada satu staff yg stand by di sekitar pintu akses ke kamar dan memberi bantuan saat tamu pertama x menggunakan aplikasi utk buka kunci pintu. Saat sy akan masuk ke area kamar, ada bbrp tamu yg sudah lanjut usia (gak tua sih, tp berumur yg pasti), mereka tampak agak kesulitan. To be noted, gak semua org update ttg teknologi lho. Mereka tampak kesulitan tp tdk ada yg aware. Awalnya kami ikut mengantri di belakang, tp karena mereka g jg berhasil dalam 3-4x mencoba akhirnya suami sy yg mencoba baru bisa di kali kedua. Lalu mereka ikut masuk semua bersama kami, sambil bergurau "untung ada masnya yg muda jd bisa yah, klo kami ini org tua gak paham ginian mas, susah jadi..." . Well, jgn sampai maksud memudahkan malah jd mempersulit ya... tamu bukan bodoh, cm blom terbiasa dan perlu diarahin atau dicontohin 1-2x.
3. Pour water di kamar, mungkim bisa dijelaskan bahwa air dikamar bisa diisi ulang dari dispenser yg diletakan di tiap lorong. Karena lagi2 sy mendengar tamu bergurau ttg "masa dikasihnya teko yah? Isinya dikit pula..." dan juga sepertinya agak kurang wise di masa pandemi, dimana semua org lebih hati2 dan aware dgn hygine dan kesterilan diri. Teko dan gelas d kamar akan menjadi pertanyaan apakah aman, apakah steril, apakah terjamin, dll.
4. Staff gak tanggap! Saat kami datang, gak dibantu sama skali, padahal bawaan kami lumayan lho! Dan di entrance itu ada 2 orang! Sampai ke kamar kami sangat mandiri dan terlihat tamu lain jg begitu. Staff terlihat abai dan gak aware sama kondisi tamunya. Cuma ada 1 staff yg agak sensitif selama saya d hotel ini, sepertinya engineering ya krn outfit dan perkakas yg dibawa. Staff eng ini berpapasan dgn saya dan suami yg terlihat mencari kamar, lalu menanyakan dan memberi arahan, lalu mengucapkan "have a nice stay, pak bu". Hal kecil dan simple namun menunjukan kepedulian dan membuat hati senang lho! Kenapa yg lain gak bisa begitu???
5. Saat co, tidak ada kata2 terima kasih, sampai jumpa lg, atau kata2 lain yg memberi kesan keramahtamahan  saya dan suami dibiarkan plas-plas aja gtu, hehe... gak ngarep sih, cuma ky "gak hotel banget" yg biasanya punya byk kata2 semanis madu. Cuma satu orang security yg kebetulan berdiri di area lift yg tersenyum. Tapi sama juga tanpa membantu. Dr saya injak kaki pertama hingga pulang, g sedikit pun tawaran membantu barang2 bawaan tercetus dr staff di sini. Gak ngerti apakah ini memelang jd standar hotel yg mentreat tamu mandiri apa gimana ya..
6. Handuknya, kuning dan kasar. 
So far, itu yg saya ingat. Gak byk fasilitas yg kami nikmati mengingat kami hanya singgah utk urusan kerjaan dan hanya menginap semalam, tanpa b'fast karena lbh tertarik berburu kuliner lokal. Semoga bisa diperhatikan hal2 tersebut di atas ya. Hotelnya bagus so far, jd semoga service bisa lbh baik.

Saya,istri dan 3 anak dibawah umur 11 tahun mencari kamar hotel di Semarang yang mempunyai kamar keluarga atau yang ada connecting room dan lokasi strategis untuk menginap 1 malam sebagai transit kami pergi ke Yogyakarta dari Jakarta.
Pencarian saya berakhir setelah saya menemukan hotel ini. Dengan foto-foto yang menarik,akhirnya saya memesan 1 set kamar dengan fitur connecting room dengan harga Rp 1.500.000/set.(-)

text:
I stayed in rooms inc twice for a business trip July 2017 and mid of August 2017, it's a new concept of an upscale hotel in the heart of Semarang city. For the hotel itself they have applied app-based check-in (cardless check-in) which I am sure they are the first hotel in Semarang who has it! 

Overall the hotel interior and design were just perfect for a millennial and dynamic individual traveler. You will also see many art things when you come to this hotel. Their lobby lounge area called Grab&GO offered variants of F&B product with a take-away concept even tho this outlet was not open yet on my last visit but the barista offered me with a cup of piccolo latte and had a small talk about the outlet itself, their coffee taste good!

I believe in the future this place will be perfect as well for a co-worker space who needs a unique yet inspiring working environment with full-speed wifi connection, oh for that one especially I really love their wifi connection btw since I should keep connecting to my other things in Jakarta at the same time! 

Another good value they have is the Verve Bistro & Coffee bar, located right next to the playroom (yes this hotel has a playroom guys, you can choose whether to play a billiard or table soccer) back to verve, it's the only one all day dining in this hotel. They offered Indonesian, Japanese and Western menu, I tried their buffet breakfast, and had dinner as well (ordered for their squid roll char-kway and rawon surabaya) all taste good!! Same as other restaurant or hotel, they also need to improve their speed in service for the rest nothing but the fun that you will experience while you dine in this hotel restaurant. 

Best spot in this hotel are their alfresco area of Verve Bistro & Coffee bar and another one the balcony which facing to the iconic Lawang Sewu, best time: afternoon to evening time. 

So, I can't wait for my next visit to this city and hotel again, Semarang and this hotel both always surprising me!

Coffee is complimentary during the stay, just make sure you asked for it at Reception. There is no phone in the room, so all requests and communications are through WhatsApp.
The breakfast is not bad for a small hotel. It's just a bit hard to get sunny side fried egg (it came up scrambled) and when sugar bowl is empty (for coffee and tea), the staff just shrugged and says "habis" without any attempt to replenish.
Other than that, the hotel has great location. Short walk to Lawang Sewu. Easy access to other tourist objects in the city. DP Mall is adjacent to the hotel for some quick shopping therapy.

text:
I upgraded my room from Standard to Deluxe, because the Standard room was below other hotels' standard with similar price points
The room was too small, until I always need to pass through the bed if I want to walk from the door to the window across the room. No table nor chair for you to work, only bed, tv, and luggage table. No clothes hanger as well! I mean, you can just put a hanger place above the luggage table's area

Hence, I upgraded my room to Deluxe (biggest room) to get, at least, a place for me to work with my laptop
Deluxe room was very spacious, looks very instagramable and playful. Coffee maker, refrigerator, long table, sofa, etc. I have no complain for this room.

The one that bothered me was the cleaning service.
I have been traveled to many hotels around Indonesia, from budget to luxury hotels.
In other hotels, I don't know how they find out, the cleaning service always make my room when I was away.
In this hotel, they already knock at 9am, the time when I usually in the bathroom or still sleeping (because I worked until late night or even dawn). After I did not respond, they will come back an hour later even after I put the "not now please" sign on my door.
Since you have whatsapp method for communication, maybe you can utilize that to ask your guest before clean their room. Or, just come back in every 3 hours, such as 9, 12, and 3.

Overall:
(+)
- Very good interior design, industrial theme with millenials touch, there is so many spots for taking photos
- Good breakfast, I like the penne and fried dory
- Very spacious Deluxe room
- Good location, you only go 1 floor downstair to enter the DP mall, less than 10 minutes walk to Paragon Mall, and less than 5 minutes walk to Lawang Sewu
- Also near from Panandaran, souvenir's center

(-)
- Quite pricey, with standard room price you actually can get bigger room in nearby hotel, L*uis K*enne or A*ton In*
- Room service food served with box, I think there should be differences between room service and take away order, or maybe I'm too old fashioned?
- The main / parking gate is one with the mall, hence it's not 24 hours. I had difficulty to order food via GoFood since I need to go downstairs and walking to the main gate and waiting for GoFood. Cannot make room service order since it closed at 10pm.

In overall, I like this hotel with all the design and everything, since I am a millenials person which also the reason why I was curious and booked this hotel.
I might come back again for traveling purpose, not for business, so I can take as many pictures as possible in the hotel.

Your room key is needed to access the door that leads to the elevator and access to the elevator, a sense of security. They only issued 1 room key and should you need another key you can download an app and use e-key instead. Room is standard. Not too small but not room-y either. Since this hotel is relatively new, you can expect a superb cleanliness. What kinda disappoint me is that there is no proper table within the room. The gap between the edge of the bed and the wall where the TV is mounted is way too small. So if you sleep on the window side you will either have to squeeze through the small gap or crouch over the other person. There is no safe deposit box located within the room as well. 

Breakfast is okay. I wish they could widen the selection, but the quality of the food is great. However, there was this one lady who seemed to be rather elsewhere than to work at the restaurant. She gave me quite an attitude. 

This hotel aimed to attract young travelers as this hotel is playful.

So I saw the ad on some social media, and decided to give it a ride. Pretty nice, it turned out.

The location is very good, but with a catch. It’s in a same building as the DP Mall, so expect some traffic in and out. The Pemuda street is one of the busiest street in Semarang, do be advised.

Being in the same building as a mall also meant extra spacious parking, privided you don’t mind driving up some levels.

The lobby also doubles as a diner. Those who like it will like it, and those who dont, well...

What’s good:

The room (8/10)
Nice room, comfy bed, nice TV stations. Good and clean bathroom too.

The parking (8/10)
I like to drive AND park my own car, thank you.

The location (8/10)
With new traffic flow management in the city, a location with multiple access to various destination is a plus. Tip: DP Mall has a rear access. It can save your time for certain routes.

The food (8/10)
The breakfast is good. Well, as the breakfast area and the diner area is the same, I expected that the crew is alse the same (ergo the chef, too). Was not disappionted at all. Nice cooking and quick service.

So, what’s the downside?

No hot water kettle (1/10)
Sometime I just want hot water, sometimes I just want some strange, wicked, mixture I bring myself. But there’s no electric kettle whatsoever. Well, the room IS small, but a man can wish, can we?
